        <h3>What to eat after a basketball game?</h3><br />

        <p>For a fast and effective recovery you must recharge the glycogen stores,
            promote muscle growth, repair, and rehydrate.
            <br />
            <br />
        The first 60 minutes are very important for muscle recovery since
            This is when the highest assimilation of nutrients is achieved.
            The recovery diet depends on individual physical goals:
            <br />
            <br />
        – If the goal is to increase muscle size and strength,
            choose foods with high caloric density as a sandwich
            <strong>(cheese, ham, tuna, chicken, egg)</strong>, fruit salad with yogurt, rice pudding semi,
            Cereal bars <strong>(it is preferable that they also provide proteins)</strong> 
            or liquid recovery supplements.
            <br />
            <br />
